cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on enforcing data confidentiality in low-level applications in the presence of an active adversary. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper presents an approach where the programmer marks secret data by writing annotations on top-level definitions in the source code. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the programmer overhead required to restructure the application when protecting sensitive data. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper uses custom memory layout and control-flow integrity checks to prevent data leaks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category as there is no mention of machine learning in the paper.
